<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 02 at 9:33AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE FOG THIS MORNING...
Fog, locally dense, will affect the region mid to late this morning.
Visibilities will be around 1 to 2 miles, with some locations
down to one half to one quarter mile to less than a quarter mile
at times.
If driving, be prepared for variable and suddenly reduced
visibilities. Proceed with extra caution, drive slowly and allow
for extra space between vehicles. Also, use low beam headlights.</description>
